                <ns5:provenance xml:lang="en">From the artist, fl. 400, to the treasurers of the City of Amsterdam, Johan Huijdecoper and Dr Nicolaes Tulp, for the burgomasters of Amsterdam, through the mediation of Karel Godin, 30 July 1658;{Annotations by the artist on a drawing in Haarlem, Teylers Museum; Plomp in Haarlem 1997, p. 367.} first mentioned in the Burgomasters’ Chamber of the new town hall, Amsterdam, 1663;{Dapper 1663, p. 370.} temporarily stored with three other paintings from the town hall in the house of Jan Spaan, 1808;{Brugmans 1913, pp. 59-60} transferred to the Burgomasters’ Chamber of the Prinsenhof, Amsterdam;{Scheltema 1879, p. 38.} on loan to the museum from the City of Amsterdam since 1945</ns5:provenance>
